{"id":"d=origam-topic-2191//p=468b6c3801024bbc85a0627130801a9d","tags":{"__document_id":["origam-topic-2191"],"__file_type":["text/plain"],"__file_id":["c08c3809019b4309bfabe9a8ac672b1e"],"__file_part":["ca95dd4272544b0d84ad976762d3a4a3"],"__part_n":["0"],"__sect_n":["0"],"source":["origam-community"],"category":["docs"],"categoryId":["8"],"topicId":["2191"],"url":["https://community.origam.com/t/how-to-upgrade-web-application-to-owin/2191"],"title":["How To Upgrade Web Application to OWIN"]},"payload":{"url":"","schema":"20231218A","file":"content.txt","text":"# How To Upgrade Web Application to OWIN\n\nCategory: docs\nURL: https://community.origam.com/t/how-to-upgrade-web-application-to-owin/2191\n\n@system (2017-12-31 23:00:00Z):\n This article describes steps necessary to upgrade the web application to the new version, which is based on  OWIN  since version  2015.4 . Upgrade is done only once, it is not necessary to perform such operation with each release. \n   Step-by-step guide \n \n \n Make sure .NET framework in version 4.5.1 or higher is installed. \n \n \n Make sure  ASP.NET  MVC 4 is installed. Installation package is available at  http://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/details.aspx?id=30683 . \n \n \n Download an OWIN based release of the web application. \n \n \n Deploy the files from the downloaded package. \n \n \n There is an  upgrade/upgrade_2015.4.0.cmd  script in the downloaded package. Execute it directly from  upgrade  directory, It will clear the obsolete files. \n \n \n Open  web.config  and make the following changes: \n  Add new keys to \u003CappSettings\u003E tag  \n  \u003Cadd key=\u0022webPages:Version\u0022 value=\u00222.0.0.0\u0022/\u003E\n\u003Cadd key=\u0022autoFormsAuthentication\u0022 value=\u0022false\u0022/\u003E\n\u003Cadd key=\u0022enableSimpleMembership\u0022 value=\u0022false\u0022/\u003E\n  \n  Comment or remove \u003Cauthentication\u003E tag  \n  \u003C!--\u003Cauthentication mode=\u0022Forms\u0022\u003E\n    \u003Cforms name=\u0022asapAuthCookie\u0022 timeout=\u002210\u0022 /\u003E\n\u003C/authentication\u003E//--\u003E\n  \n Authentication cookie settings (including session expire timeout) are now possible to change using  Startup.cs User Management Configuration . \n  Enable access to /Login and /Recover urls  \n  \u003Clocation path=\u0022Login\u0022\u003E\n    \u003Csystem.web\u003E\n        \u003Cauthorization\u003E\n            \u003Callow users=\u0022*\u0022 /\u003E\n        \u003C/authorization\u003E\n    \u003C/system.web\u003E\n\u003C/location\u003E\n\u003Clocation path=\u0022Recover\u0022\u003E\n    \u003Csystem.web\u003E\n        \u003Cauthorization\u003E\n            \u003Callow users=\u0022*\u0022 /\u003E\n        \u003C/authorization\u003E\n    \u003C/system.web\u003E\n\u003C/location\u003E\n  \n  Add handlers  \n  \u003Cadd verb=\u0022*\u0022 path=\u0022Gateway.aspx\u0022 type=\u0022Origam.Server.Handlers.GatewayHandler, Origam.Server.Handlers\u0022 name=\u0022GatewayHandler\u0022/\u003E\n\u003Cadd verb=\u0022*\u0022 path=\u0022SignOut.ashx\u0022 type=\u0022Origam.Server.Handlers.SignOutHandler, Origam.Server.Handlers\u0022 name=\u0022SignOutHandler\u0022/\u003E\n\u003Cadd verb=\u0022*\u0022 path=\u0022ReportProblem.ashx\u0022 type=\u0022Origam.Server.Handlers.ReportProblemHandler, Origam.Server.Handlers\u0022 name=\u0022ReportProblemHandler\u0022/\u003E\n\u003Cadd verb=\u0022*\u0022 path=\u0022GeoLocation.ashx\u0022 type=\u0022Origam.Server.Handlers.GeoLocationHandler, Origam.Server.Handlers\u0022 name=\u0022GeoLocationHandler\u0022/\u003E\n  \n  Set default document as Portal.cshtml  \n  \u003CdefaultDocument\u003E\n    \u003Cfiles\u003E\n        \u003Cclear/\u003E\n        \u003Cadd value=\u0022Portal.cshtml\u0022/\u003E\n    \u003C/files\u003E\n\u003C/defaultDocument\u003E\n  \n \n \n Configure OWIN container through  Startup.cs  file. Its location is expected in  App_Code  folder of the application. Sample file is provided with the package as  Startup.cs_ . Sample file contains configuration for cookie authorization via  Asp.Net  Membership provider. \n \n \n Switch the application to the application pool based on .NET 4.0. \n \n \n Make sure you have a record in the  BusinessPartner  table with  UserName=  \u0022\u0060\u0060guest\u0022.  \n \n \n If your application was configured to use  Asp.Net  Membership provider, your work is done and you should be able to log in to the system. \n If your application is using AJAX login and sign out functionality, you need to update URLs. They\u2019re changed from  /AjaxLogin.ashx  and  /AjaxSignOut.ashx  to  /AjaxLogin  and  /AjaxSignOut . \n   Related Articles \n \n \n Page: \n  Startup.cs User Management Configuration  (ORIGAM Documentation) - This article provides information on configuration of user management in Origam application. \n \n \n Page: \n  Email Address Confirmation  (ORIGAM Documentation) \n \n \n Page: \n  How To Upgrade Web Application to OWIN  (ORIGAM Documentation) \n \n \n Page: \n  How to Migrate from Membership to Origam Based Authentication  (ORIGAM Documentation) \n \n \n   Comments: \n \n\n\n\n \n \n  @washi Why is there a default document in web.config if we need to set it up also in Startup.cs? \n \nPosted by admin at Apr 15, 2015 17:37\n  \n \n \n  Because web.config configures IIS, while Startup.cs configures OWIN. ","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-04-29T00:23:48"},"vector":[-0.040637877,0.014855633,-0.039284863,0.004771524,0.008908178,-0.03959747,0.016275084,-0.00031029733,-0.010962166,0.020712607,0.009061375,-0.0044486746,-0.023047594,0.02314328,0.004753955,-0.022406895,-0.023825182,0.031524844,0.01280958,0.022037892,-0.022765134,-0.024622755,0.041149337,0.030978901,0.00868367,0.005341182,0.021739533,-0.02175998,0.046815794,-0.002625967,0.012631661,-0.06516993,-0.049532708,-0.069780156,-0.0030124967,-0.011041511,0.016585087,0.0015905129,-0.044719443,0.003440696,0.025146257,-0.0464